CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, March 10, 1956, pg. 26, reads: "Farewell to Si - Tabbed everybody's All-American and labeled by coach Dudley Moore as the greatest basketball player he has ever seen, Sihugo Green ended his home career, scoring 29 points and leading the Dukes to a 64-56 win over St. Bonaventure at the Gardens Monday....At the right [left], Si and his coach, Dudley Moore, shake hands in mutual admiration. - Harris photos."
TitMainTitle: Duquesne basketball player Sihugo "Si" Green, shaking hands with coach Dudley Moore, in Duquesne Gardens
